In a #small pot{}, bring 1 cup salted water to a boil. Once boiling, add the @Jasmine Rice{1/2%cup}, cover, and simmer for ~{15-20%minutes}, until tender. Remove from the heat and keep covered until the rest of the meal is ready.

Mince or grate the @Garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Halve, seed, and remove the white ribs from the @Green Bell Pepper{1}(halved, seeded, and finely diced), then finely dice. Halve, peel, and dice the @Red Onion{1}(halved, peeled, and diced). Thinly slice the @Scallions{2}(thinly sliced), keeping the whites and the greens separate. Core and dice the @Roma Tomato{1}(cored and diced). Drain and rinse the @Black Beans{1%13.4oz can}.

Heat @Olive Oil{2%tablespoon} in a large #pan{} over medium heat. Add the pepper, onion, and scallion whites and cook, tossing for ~{3-5%minutes}, until softened. Add the garlic, tomatoes, and @Chipotle Seitan Crumbles{8%ounce} to the pan, and cook for ~{3-5%minutes}, breaking up the seitan into small pieces.

Add the beans to the #pot{} along with the @Veggie Stock Concentrate{1} and 1 cup water. Simmer for ~{5-7%minutes}, until thickened. Season with @Salt{to taste} and @Pepper{to taste}.

> TIP: If you have time, let the chili simmer longer. The flavors will get even better!

Serve the chipotle seitan chili on a bed of jasmine rice and garnish with the reserved scallion greens and @Cheddar Cheese{2%ounce}(gooey).